Write a simple script to take the system backup and store it in a tar.gz archive. 
Change the archive permission to user_read_only. Schedule a cronjob so that the 
script run everyday at 1 am.

#!/bin/bash

# Get the current date and time
date=$(date +%Y-%m-%d-%H-%M)

# Create the backup archive
tar -cvzf backup-$date.tar.gz /

# Change the archive permission to user_read_only
chmod 444 backup-$date.tar.gz

# Schedule the script to run everyday at 1 am
crontab -e

# Add the following line to the crontab file
0 1 * * * /path/to/backup.sh
